<div class="container mt-5">
   <u> <h1>Features of NoteWave</h1><br></u>
    
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Attractive Front Page</h2>
            <p>
                The front page of NoteWave is designed to be visually appealing and user-friendly. It features a clean, modern layout with an intuitive design that welcomes users and immediately communicates the purpose of the app. Key elements include a compelling hero section with a call-to-action button, an overview of features, and a simple navigation menu. The use of vibrant colors, typography, and high-quality graphics ensures a pleasant and engaging user experience right from the start.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Google Authentication</h2>
            <p>
                Google Authentication provides a secure and convenient way for users to log in to NoteWave. By integrating with Google Sign-In, users can quickly access their accounts without the need to remember additional passwords. This feature leverages Google's OAuth 2.0 framework to ensure a safe and streamlined login process, enhancing user security and reducing friction during account creation and login.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Search</h2>
            <p>
                The search feature allows users to efficiently find notes or information within NoteWave. Users can enter keywords to quickly locate specific notes or tags, making it easy to retrieve relevant information. The search functionality supports real-time results as users type, offering suggestions and improving the overall efficiency of note retrieval.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Pagination</h2>
            <p>
                Pagination is implemented to manage and display large sets of notes in a user-friendly manner. Instead of overwhelming users with a long list of notes, pagination divides the content into manageable chunks or pages. Users can navigate through pages to view more notes, improving load times and making it easier to find specific entries without scrolling endlessly.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Create Notes</h2>
            <p>
                The "Create Notes" feature allows users to add new notes to their collection. This functionality provides a straightforward and user-friendly interface for composing and saving notes. Users can enter text, add formatting, and optionally include tags or categories. The ability to create notes quickly and efficiently is central to the utility of NoteWave.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Update Notes</h2>
            <p>
                Users can easily update and edit their existing notes using the "Update Notes" feature. This functionality allows for changes to the content of a note, including text edits, formatting adjustments, and re-tagging. Whether correcting a mistake or adding new information, users have full control over their notes, ensuring that their data remains accurate and up-to-date.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>Delete Notes</h2>
            <p>
                The "Delete Notes" feature provides users with the ability to remove notes they no longer need. This option is essential for maintaining an organized and clutter-free note collection. Users can select and delete individual notes or perform batch deletions, ensuring that their note-taking experience remains efficient and relevant.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
            <h2>View Notes</h2>
            <p>
                The "View Notes" feature allows users to access and read their saved notes. This functionality displays the contents of selected notes in a clear and readable format. Users can browse through their notes, view details, and utilize any included tags or categories to navigate their note collection effectively.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
